 tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uyo1665702691073.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uyo1665702691073.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uyo1665702691073.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uyo1665702691073\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Message API Utility\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"uyo1665702691073__message_api_utility_103539\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Message API Utility sends messages to a Uniface application from a non-Uniface Windows application using Uniface's remote <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">postmessage</span> mechanism.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyo1665702691073__p_d31724e1_d31725e1_d31726e1\">The utility activates an internal Uniface component, which sends an asynchronous message to the component instance specified. The message is placed in the event queue of the receiving application, from where it is delivered to the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">receiveMessage</span> trigger of the specified component instance.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uyo1665702691073__p_d31727e1_d31728e1_d31729e1\">The utility can be accessed via the command line (<span class=\"ph filepath\">umsgutil.exe</span>) or via an ActiveX component (<span class=\"ph filepath\">unimsg.ocx</span>). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nhr1665702690996.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nhr1665702690996.html\" title=\"Command line interface for the Message API Utility.\">umsgutil.exe</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"usj1665702691142.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/usj1665702691142.html\" title=\"The unimsg.ocx file is the ActiveX component that allows you to access the Message API Utility.\">unimsg.ocx</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532909\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532909\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Message API Utility Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Message API Utility The Message API Utility sends messages to a Uniface application from a non-Uniface Windows application using Uniface's remote postmessage mechanism. The utility activates an internal Uniface component, which sends an asynchronous message to the component instance specified. The message is placed in the event queue of the receiving application, from where it is delivered to the receiveMessage trigger of the specified component instance. The utility can be accessed via the command line ( umsgutil.exe ) or via an ActiveX component ( unimsg.ocx ). For more information, see umsgutil.exe and unimsg.ocx . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}